Tic Tac Toe in Python with Tkinter

This repository contains a simple yet engaging Tic Tac Toe game written in Python, utilizing the Tkinter GUI library. The game allows for a single player to compete against a computer-controlled opponent. The computer's moves are determined through basic strategy, ensuring a challenging but fair gameplay experience.
Features

    Graphical User Interface: Utilizes Tkinter for a responsive and intuitive GUI.
    Intelligent Computer Opponent: The computer opponent makes decisions based on potential winning moves or blocks.
    Restart Functionality: Players can restart the game at any time with a dedicated button.
    Winning Condition Check: The game checks for winning conditions after every move.

How to Play

    The game starts with the player's turn, marked by 'X'. Click on any of the 9 grid buttons to make a move.
    The computer will automatically make its move as 'O' after the player.
    The game announces a winner or a tie through a label at the top of the window.
    To play again, click the "Restart" button at the top of the window.
